{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17504159","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17504159"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:11:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:11:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2303"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2303","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2303"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.2,0.68,0.01,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2303"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101387"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2303","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2303"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2303"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"83817"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"106"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"9735"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12911"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8455"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8738"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13678"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18450"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34899"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34900"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42465"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101387","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/101387"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 59-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with acute onset of palpitations and shortness of breath. He is alert, with a blood pressure of 130/90 mmHg and has an oxygen saturation of 98% breathing room air. His ECG is shown (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Left bundle branch block","Type 2 second-degree heart block","Atrial fibrillation","Non-ST-elevation myocardial infarction","Accelerated junctional escape rhythm"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis ECG demonstrates an irregular, narrow-complex rhythm. There are no discernible P waves. This is consistent with a diagnosis of \u003Cstrong\u003Eatrial fibrillation\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere is good R-wave progression with no widening of the QRS complex, and no characteristic QRS LBBB morphology in leads V1 or V5-6. There is also normal axis whereas a LBBB would be associated with a left axis deviation. Therefore there is no complete \u003Cstrong\u003Eleft bundle branch block\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlthough\u003Cstrong\u003E type 2\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003Esecond-degree heart block\u003C/strong\u003E is also associated with an irregular rhythm, P-waves would be expected in heart block, which is not seen here. P-waves in type 2 second-degree heart block occur at a constant rate. RR intervals in conducted P-waves (i.e. creates a QRS complex) remain the same length and RR intervals between dropped beats should be an exact multiple of the preceding RR interval, giving it an regularly irregular pattern, as opposed to a irregularly irregular pattern seen here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere are no ischemic changes on this ECG to suggest a \u003Cstrong\u003Enon-ST-elevation myocardial infarction\u003C/strong\u003E. If one is suspicious of an acute coronary syndrome, this should be further investigated with troponin testing.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlthough there are no P waves, this is not an \u003Cstrong\u003Eaccelerated junctional escape rhythm\u003C/strong\u003E because this rhythm is irregular.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Suspect atrial fibrillation in narrow-complex irregular rhythms with absent P waves"],"references":["Brundel BJJM et al. Atrial fibrillation. J Am Soc Nephrol. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2016 Mar 31;2:16017."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"83817"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2303"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21893"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21893","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21893"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/BhKqDZHXHRIf8xZbkMq4exyJ52JI5K.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/BhKqDZHXHRIf8xZbkMq4exyJ52JI5K.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":800,"height":414}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"83817","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/83817"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-01T18:16:21+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-01T18:17:02+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2303"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101387"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Med